pageContext.claim: “Our unemployment numbers. If it's African American, if it's Asian, if it's Hispanic, they're the best historic numbers in history -- in the history of our country they're the best numbers we've ever had.”
pageContext.analysis: The black and Hispanic unemployment rates have been calculated only since 1972, so it's an exaggeration to say the current numbers are the lowest ever. Although the black unemployment rate was at an all-time-low 5.9 percent in May, it had risen to 7 percent in February. That was still significantly higher than the overall unemployment rate of 3.8 percent.
